Introduction

Base URL: https://sado-ksa.com

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Endpoints

POST api/v1/auth/register

Example request:
curl --request POST \

    --data "{
    \"contact_person_name\": \"id\",
    \"address_type\": \"earum\",
    \"address\": \"ut\",
    \"city\": \"similique\",
    \"zip\": \"aut\",
    \"country\": \"aliquid\",
    \"phone\": \"a\",
    \"latitude\": \"aut\",
    \"longitude\": \"dolorem\",
    \"is_billing\": \"consequatur\"
}"

);

};

    "address_type": "earum",
    "address": "ut",
    "city": "similique",
    "zip": "aut",
    "country": "aliquid",
    "phone": "a",
    "latitude": "aut",
    "longitude": "dolorem",
    "is_billing": "consequatur"

    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"search_text\": \"sunt\"
}"

    "https://sado-ksa.com/api/v1/mapapi/place-api-autocomplete"
);

};

};

Example: et

  • percent

lang   string   

Example: eum

Must be at least 1 character. Example: emziur

Must be at least 1 character. Example: wmjhtzpoprbftlzgzceiimtrnblpuufrfyewrfptspdrmmnmzfmpcpytfkaafdvegyvitjxtryylclriykki

discount   string   

Example: sit

This field is required when product_type is == or physical.

code   string   

Example: nobis

  • percent

Example: perspiciatis

unit_price   string   

Must be at least 1 character. Example: rylwlkgpggvmfbtu

purchase_price   string   

Must be at least 1 character. Example: yoesmwozowtcayexhfwxwgupoalnvkttlpkkvqaahumfisldcevwtlqyfbshqozfphpm

discount   string   

Example: molestias

shipping_cost   string  optional  

This field is required when product_type is == or physical.

minimum_order_qty   number   

Must be at least 1. Example: 3

POST api/v3/seller/pos/customer-store

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "https://sado-ksa.com/api/v3/seller/pos/customer-store" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"f_name\": \"voluptas\",
    \"l_name\": \"adipisci\",
    \"email\": \"pat02@example.net\",
    \"country\": \"ea\",
    \"city\": \"expedita\",
    \"zip_code\": \"sed\",
    \"address\": \"voluptas\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://sado-ksa.com/api/v3/seller/pos/customer-store"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "f_name": "voluptas",
    "l_name": "adipisci",
    "email": "pat02@example.net",
    "country": "ea",
    "city": "expedita",
    "zip_code": "sed",
    "address": "voluptas"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:

If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.

    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('f_name', 'natus');
body.append('l_name', 'occaecati');
body.append('phone', 'ab');
body.append('image', document.querySelector('input[name="image"]').files[0]);

fetch(url, {
    method: "PUT",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
